cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with domain adaptation for recognition in the wild, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel approach that combines both feature-level and pixel-level adaptation, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses image synthesis techniques, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper validates its approach on a problem of car recognition in surveillance images, which falls under computer vision and security (cs.CR).
